-- Koller Sells Anker Painting for Record 7.5 Million Francs
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2013-06-21T17:05:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-21/koller-sells-anker-painting-for-record-7-5-million-francs.html
Koller Auctions said it sold Albert
Anker’s “ Turnstunde in Ins ” for 7.5 million Swiss francs ($8
million), a record price for the Swiss painter.  Vincent Van Gogh’s “Pont de Clichy” sold for 6.6 million
francs, the Zurich auction house said.  Total sales at the auction today reached 30 million francs,
the firm said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
